TV presenter Katlego Maboe is finally making a comeback to the entertainment industry after a tumultuous two years after his romantic relationship made headlines for all the wrong reasons. Katlego received the backlash after a video of him wearing a purple gown and arguing with his partner went viral on social media. In January, he shared a statement about his court woes finally coming to an end. The statement read that he was absolved by the magistrate’s court against the allegations of misconduct made by his former partner Monique Muller in October 2020. Beaming with excitement, he took to social media on Thursday to share that he was excited about the next chapter of his life. In his post, Katlego hinted that he would be working with The Wife actor Linda Majola and Dr Tshidi Gule at The Wellness Plug. The Wellness Plug is a new podcast that will be broadcast in April and focuses on inspiring healthy conversations. “Grateful for everyone who has opened a door, said a prayer, and helped me to keep believing. May God bless this journey,” he wrote.  Also Read: Katlego Maboe’s two year legal battle over For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.